{
  "text": "Furan-2-carbaldehyde (1 mmol) and phenylacetonitrile (1 mmol) were dissolved in dry ethanol (10 mL). After that, sodium hydroxide (0.1 mmol) was added and stirred for 5 min at room temperature under nitrogen atmosphere. The precipitated yellow solid was filtered, washed with ethanol, and recrystallized in CHCl3 to give pure product 1 as light yellow crystals [CITATION_1] ",
